In large saucepan or Dutch oven, melt butter over medium-low heat. Add marshmallows; cook, stirring constantly until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter. Add crispy rice cereal; stir to coat evenly. Lightly press half of mixture (about 31/2 cups) into sprayed or buttered 8x8-inch pan. Sprinkle and lightly press down Snickers pieces. Top with remaining crispy rice mixture and press down. Melt chocolate chips in microwave. Drizzle over bars. Cool for 30 minutes; cut into 16 bars.